Seq1.CallerContent: Hi, I need to make an appointment, please.

Seq2.ReceiverContent: Okay, would you like to meet the doctor in person or would you like to make a televisit?

Seq3.ReceiverContent: Okay, let me check on the next available slot for you. Okay.

Seq4.CallerContent: I have tonsillitis, so no, that's not going to work for me.
Seq4.ReceiverContent: When do you like to make it?

Seq5.CallerContent: I mean, like tomorrow at the latest.
Seq5.ReceiverContent: Latest, one moment. Before 20th of November, we don't have any slots available to make up an appointment.

Seq6.CallerContent: No. You don't have any, like, emergency sick visit slots? Yeah.
Seq6.ReceiverContent: Emergency. Okay, one moment. Can you come to the office tomorrow in the afternoon?

Seq7.ReceiverContent: At 2.30 p.m. Will that be okay with you?

Seq8.ReceiverContent: Your first name is Kathleen, am I correct?

Seq9.ReceiverContent: And may I know the reason of the appointment?

Seq10.CallerContent: I went to urgent care and was diagnosed with either strep throat or tonsillitis, and it's not getting any better.
Seq10.ReceiverContent: So is this going to be a follow-up?

Seq11.ReceiverContent: Just to confirm, I have an appointment tomorrow at 2.30 p.m. to meet the doctor in person.

Seq12.ReceiverContent: Is there anything else that I missed, Judith?

Seq13.ReceiverContent: Thank you for calling Carole from Family Practice. You have a great day.
